    • getAt

      public static <T> T getAt​(@org.checkerframework.checker.index.qual.NonNegative int index, @NotNull @NotNull List<T> list, @Nullable @Nullable Supplier<T> ifInvalidIndexFallbackSupplier, @Nullable @Nullable Supplier<T> ifNullFallbackSupplier)

      Returns the element at the specified movedToIndex using optional Fallback Suppliers to handle various types of invalid queries.

      LOGIC OVERVIEW

      1. List is Null
        • Throw a NullPointerException.
      2. Index is Valid
        • Retrieve the element at the specified movedToIndex.
          1. Element is Not Null
            • Return the element.
          2. Element is Null
            • If the ifNullFallbackSupplier is non-null, return its value.
            • If the ifNullFallbackSupplier is null, throw a new NullPointerException.
      3. Index is Invalid
        • If the ifInvalidIndexFallbackSupplier is non-null, return its value.
        • If the ifInvalidIndexFallbackSupplier is null, throw a new IndexOutOfBoundsException.
      Type Parameters:
      T - The type of element contained in the specified List.

      Also the type of Object returned by this method.

      Parameters:
      index - The movedToIndex to retrieve the desired element from.
      list - The List from which the returned element is retrieved.
      ifInvalidIndexFallbackSupplier - An optional Supplier that is called if the specified movedToIndex is invalid for any reason.
      ifNullFallbackSupplier - An optional Supplier that is called if the element at the specified movedToIndex is null.
      Returns:
      The element at the specified movedToIndex in the specified List.

      See documentation body for details.

      Throws:
      IndexOutOfBoundsException - If the specified movedToIndex is a negative value.
      NullPointerException - If the specified List is null.
      IndexOutOfBoundsException - If the specified movedToIndex is not within the bounds of the specified List and the ifInvalidIndexFallbackSupplier was not specified.
      NullPointerException - If the element at the specified movedToIndex is null and the ifNullFallbackSupplier was not specified.

    • getLongestIndex

      public static <T> Point getLongestIndex​(ArrayList<T> arr, ArrayList<T> subArr)
      Searches the specified ArrayList for the largest portion of the specified sub ArrayList. The portion of the sub ArrayList that is found always starts at element 0.
      Type Parameters:
      T - The type of the ArrayLists
      Parameters:
      arr - The base ArrayList.
      subArr - The ArrayList that is being searched for.
      Returns:
      A point representing the location of the sub array. The x coordinate of the point is the movedToIndex of the first matching element in the base array that was found, the y coordinate is the last matching element in the base array that was found.
